atha. Kharif There are three cropping seasons (Rabi, Kharif-I or Pre-Kharif, and Kharif-II) in Bangladesh. Machas A", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "018fbee3-cd9a-4716-93e4-e191341a08d6": {"__data__": {"id_": "018fbee3-cd9a-4716-93e4-e191341a08d6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/aphdr-technical-background-paper-2012/09", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "APHDR Technical Background Paper 2012/09", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/aphdr-technical-background-paper-2012/09", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "076c3666b27063cc79b4e8bb116f810acd32dc2ae9fd86a6af988838e3f34599"}, "3": {"node_id": "7c274508-cc22-46fa-9377-e94eeb517f94", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/aphdr-technical-background-paper-2012/09", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "22392a507e3ed6723c30c949f25df5a617e3a5314963ac8dda7230383ecdb4ce"}}, "hash": "7ff5128ba5ad1a047dba12d63cd6e5dadb545325ec30c5765526e13134030b4d", "text": "higher place where people can store/preserve their food and fuel. Maunds Local unit of weight in Bangladesh, 1 maund = 37.5kg. Nakshikatha Embroidered quilts, bedspreads, wall hangings, and pillow shams made by artists in rural Bangladesh. Nakshikatha is a folk art that has been passed down through generations of Bangladeshi families. It takes tatters, cotton and needles to weav