kely to decline sharply. India is expected to increase its share from 16% in 2005 to 18.2% in 2030 indicating higher future growth in energy demand. Among the selected countries, many are projected to experience higher growth in primary energy demand during 2015-30 compared to 2005-15. This may be due to the imperative of economic growth in these countries. 17 Table 6: Primary energy demand (MTOE) outlook", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "87196dca-a277-4b48-aa5c-ee9d6cf067ff": {"__data__": {"id_": "87196dca-a277-4b48-aa5c-ee9d6cf067ff", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/aphdr-technical-background-paper-2012/17", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "APHDR Technical Background Paper 2012/17", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/aphdr-technical-background-paper-2012/17", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "b61c1e5dfea847ee5f70a7af782becbadbfec4cdef2c71d4c22bc81da7594711"}, "3": {"node_id": "fdbb6bab-ea25-46c1-b45a-129fa84ffc06", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/aphdr-technical-background-paper-2012/17", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "07871be02f9ee76c854faaae1d487fd842a25e6cc32f0c338e154e87e19997f6"}}, "hash": "c6481b91c2784ca662c12cba38c2cb3848e533f174223ea1b86048566afe1954", "text": "for selected countries and Asia-Pacific region Country 1990 2000 2005 2006 2015 2030 Gro